abstract: Iowa State University prohibited political slogans on sidewalks after students complained that the messages had become discriminatory and divisive.
snippet: Iowa State University prohibited political slogans on sidewalks after students complained that the messages had become discriminatory and divisive.
lead_paragraph: AMES, Iowa — The well-trodden pathways at Iowa State University are usually caked with chalk during an election year. Students streaming past the domed administration building, hunched against the biting cold, could look down at their phones and expect to see “Trump 2020” or “Pete!” in dusty block letters.

abstract: Seemingly nonpolitical topics can shed light on political preferences.
snippet: Seemingly nonpolitical topics can shed light on political preferences.
lead_paragraph: When was the last time you had vindaloo or tandoori chicken? Chances are if you’re a Democrat in Iowa supporting Joe Biden, it has been a while.

abstract: Massachusetts Sen. Elizabeth Warren joined former Vice President Joe Biden on Wednesday in a presidential campaign pledge to avoid the use of fake news, manipulated images or online misinformation.
snippet: Massachusetts Sen. Elizabeth Warren joined former Vice President Joe Biden on Wednesday in a presidential campaign pledge to avoid the use of fake news, manipulated images or online misinformation.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Massachusetts Sen. Elizabeth Warren joined former Vice President Joe Biden on Wednesday in a presidential campaign pledge to avoid the use of fake news, manipulated images or online misinformation.
headline_main: Misinformation Pledge Gains a Supporter in Presidential Race
headline_print_headline: Misinformation Pledge Gains a Supporter in Presidential Race

abstract: O.K., maybe there will be a clear winner on Monday night. But let me explain what else might happen.
snippet: O.K., maybe there will be a clear winner on Monday night. But let me explain what else might happen.
lead_paragraph: AMES, Iowa — Driving through the snowy cornfields of Iowa today, I couldn’t stop dreaming about next Tuesday, the day after the Iowa caucuses. After more than a year of campaign entrances and exits, debates and dance moves, we’ll finally get some real clarity about this crowded Democratic primary race.

headline_print_headline: One Winner, or Maybe Two or Three

abstract: Four Democratic senators running for president have been dashing between the campaign trail and the impeachment trial.
snippet: Four Democratic senators running for president have been dashing between the campaign trail and the impeachment trial.
lead_paragraph: Four Democratic senators running for president — Senators Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren, Amy Klobuchar and Michael Bennet — have been dashing between the campaign trail and the impeachment trial in Washington. The frantic schedule appeared to be catching up with Mr. Sanders, who is leading recent polls in Iowa.

headline_main: A frantic campaign schedule appears to catch up with one senator.

abstract: Joe Biden will deliver a speech on Thursday forcefully rebuking the president, whose allies in Congress have increasingly set their sights on the former vice president.
snippet: Joe Biden will deliver a speech on Thursday forcefully rebuking the president, whose allies in Congress have increasingly set their sights on the former vice president.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., after coming under assault at the impeachment trial, plans on Thursday to offer a forceful rebuke of President Trump that will double as a closing message ahead of the Iowa caucuses on Monday.

abstract: Most presidential candidates try to manage expectations in the final stretch of a campaign knowing a surprise win is always better than an expected one. Not Bernie Sanders.
snippet: Most presidential candidates try to manage expectations in the final stretch of a campaign knowing a surprise win is always better than an expected one. Not Bernie Sanders.
lead_paragraph: SIOUX CITY, Iowa — Most presidential candidates try to manage expectations in the final stretch of a campaign knowing a surprise win is always better than an expected one. Not Bernie Sanders.
headline_main: 'How Good I Feel': Sanders Setting High Expectations in Iowa
headline_print_headline: 'How Good I Feel': Sanders Setting High Expectations in Iowa

abstract: Democratic officials and some activists for the candidate say Joe Biden’s Iowa organization is weak in some areas, which could hurt him on caucus night. Biden aides say they have plenty of boots on the ground.
snippet: Democratic officials and some activists for the candidate say Joe Biden’s Iowa organization is weak in some areas, which could hurt him on caucus night. Biden aides say they have plenty of boots on the ground.
lead_paragraph: DUBUQUE, Iowa — This city on the bluffs of the Mississippi River, which rose as a hub of furniture-making and brewing, ought to be a stronghold for Joseph R. Biden Jr. It is a blue-collar enclave with a Catholic heritage, aligning with his working class pitch to voters. Its 31-year-old, labor-connected congresswoman, Abby Finkenauer, has endorsed Mr. Biden.
